             <h3>
              Grade "A" Safety Rating
             </h3>
             <p>
              We are very proud to have been recognized with an "A" safety rating from The Leapfrog Group. Newton-Wellesley Hospital is one of only 72 hospitals in the entire country to score straight A's for three consecutive years.
             </p>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12">
             <h3>
              Grant's Story: Thoracic Outlet Syndrome
             </h3>
             <p>
              <span>
               MIT Freshman Grant Fuhr has been a competitive swimmer since age 5.  The sport he loves finally caught up with him. The computer science student and varsity swimmer from Des Moines had just returned to his college dorm from swim practice when he felt an unusual pain in his chest. “One minute I was taking a test, the next I was being whisked away to Newton-Wellesley Hospital.” At Newton-Wellesley’s pediatric emergency department, Fuhr met vascular surgeon Christopher Kwolek, MD, who “explained everything that was about to happen, with a calm and reassuring voice. I felt like I was in good hands."
              </span>
             </p>
            </div>
           </div>
          </a>
         </div>
         <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 col-md-4">

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12">
             <h3>
              Ron's Story: Aneurysm Repair
             </h3>
             <p>
              <span>
               Seventy-seven-year-old Ron Mongeon says he's always enjoyed good health. When he woke up with severe stomach cramps, he knew something wasn’t right. "As the day went on I was feeling worse and worse," explains Ron. "My wife told me that it was time to go to the emergency room. When you’ve been married as long as I have you listen to your wife!"
              </span>
             </p>
            </div>
           </div>
          </a>
         </div>
         <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 col-md-4">

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12">
             <h3>
              Aubrey's Story: Weight Loss Surgery
             </h3>
             <p>
              <span>
               At 22 years old and 351 lbs, Aubrey Podell was nearly incapable of regular, daily activities. She was classified as "super morbidly obese," and on track to develop type 2 diabetes, high blood pressure and heart disease all before she reached the age of 30.
              </span>
             </p>
            </div>
           </div>
          </a>
